          <img alt="DistRap logo" src='img/logo.svg'>
        .span6

      .row-fluid
        .span6
          %p
            Welcome to the world of distributed control!

            DistRap is the umbrella community project aiming to
            provide robust solution for implementing various control systems
            in distributed manner.

          %h3 Why distributed?
          %p
            Currently available systems often hit limitations of controller boards
            either in scalability, firmware capacity or complexity needed for further
            extension.
            Inspired by Unix philosophy, DistRap nodes should do one thing and do it well
            and communicate with each other over shared bus.
            Such system should provide extensible and robust solution for hobby or industrial
            automation allowing control of wide range of machines.

          %h3 Future is closed loop
          %p
            DistRap servo controllers offer closed-loop servo functionality with feedback back to
            master node. This can greatly improve safety and reliability of your machine or whole
            control system.

